<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-26T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-26T09:00:00-05:00" n="191" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.4111/55: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-26T15:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 26, 1919,
                                        3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 26,
                                    2.07 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>2130. I am today telegraphing Mr. Lansing in Paris as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“In view of the approaching visit of the Prince of Wales to
                                    Canada in August, I earnestly suggest that official invitation
                                    be extended to him to visit the United States. The sooner this
                                    is done the better the effect.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>